posts.post_content:
@Eppek\_the\_Goblin  
If your opponent is seriously playing [Island Fish Jasconius](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Island Fish Jasconius), then you needn't be afraid of him winning. Just don't play [Islands](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Islands) or play a [Wall of Frost](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Wall of Frost) or win the game before turn 7. The Island Fish is a classic, but it sucks.  
Anyway, this card stinks when you compare it to [Shield of Duty and Reason](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Shield of Duty and Reason) or [Flickering Ward](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Flickering Ward).
